### Volume Mounts

**Essential volumes:**

| Volume                                                        | Purpose                     | Required |
|---------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------|----------|
| `~/.config/{{CONFIG_DIR_NAME}}:/root/.config/{{CONFIG_DIR_NAME}}` | Configuration & credentials | Yes      |
| `$(pwd):/workspace`                                           | Current directory access    | Optional |

**Example with workspace mount:**

```bash
docker run -it --rm \
  -v ~/.config/{{CONFIG_DIR_NAME}}:/root/.config/{{CONFIG_DIR_NAME}} \
  -v $(pwd):/workspace \
  -w /workspace \
  {{DOCKER_IMAGE_NAME}} [COMMAND]
```

### Security Considerations

- Configuration files are stored in `~/.config/{{CONFIG_DIR_NAME}}` on your host machine
- Never commit `.config/{{CONFIG_DIR_NAME}}` to version control
- Ensure file permissions are restrictive: `chmod 700 ~/.config/{{CONFIG_DIR_NAME}}`
{{#if AUTH_REQUIRED}}
- Use API tokens instead of passwords for authentication
